00:56:16.140 --> 00:56:17.630
works.

00:56:17.630 --> 00:56:19.640
David Bohm, I
think, actually was

00:56:19.640 --> 00:56:24.050
credited by rewriting EPR,
who essentially talked

00:56:24.050 --> 00:56:28.580
about position and momenta
to talk about spins.

00:56:28.580 --> 00:56:30.500
And he might have been
the first one that

00:56:30.500 --> 00:56:33.090
began to try to do
hidden variable theory.

00:56:33.090 --> 00:56:36.610
But no hidden variable
theory works at this moment.

00:56:36.610 --> 00:56:38.780
And this shows it.

00:56:38.780 --> 00:56:42.680
So people say that
actually this assumes

00:56:42.680 --> 00:56:47.130
that there's local
hidden variable theories

00:56:47.130 --> 00:56:49.140
and there's non-local
hidden variable

00:56:49.140 --> 00:56:51.290
theories and all kinds
of strange things.

00:56:51.290 --> 00:56:53.760
But it's more and
more unnatural.

00:56:53.760 --> 00:56:56.440
So it doesn't seem to do
something very interesting.

00:56:56.440 --> 00:56:57.690
Yes, there are many questions.

00:56:57.690 --> 00:56:59.586
Aaron, maybe you want
to say something.

00:56:59.586 --> 00:57:02.442
STUDENT: Let's see, I think Bohm
has a non-local hidden variable

00:57:02.442 --> 00:57:03.400
theory solution.

00:57:03.400 --> 00:57:04.610
It's kind of awful looking.

00:57:04.610 --> 00:57:09.696
But I guess violates the
second principle rather than

00:57:09.696 --> 00:57:10.694
the first one.

00:57:10.694 --> 00:57:14.851
It also doesn't extend
to-- this doesn't really

00:57:14.851 --> 00:57:15.684
work for everything.

00:57:15.684 --> 00:57:19.343
We don't know how to make it
work for a spin-1/2 particle

00:57:19.343 --> 00:57:23.169
to find [? a dimension. ?] So
[INTERPOSING VOICES] really

00:57:23.169 --> 00:57:26.670
believe to be a true theory
of [? equivalence. ?]

00:57:26.670 --> 00:57:28.610
PROFESSOR: Thank you.

00:57:28.610 --> 00:57:30.810
More questions.

00:57:30.810 --> 00:57:32.244
Steve?

00:57:32.244 --> 00:57:36.334
STUDENT: In the case with EPR,
is it a problem that we can

00:57:36.334 --> 00:57:40.070
have scenarios where the spin
is greater than a spin-1/2

00:57:40.070 --> 00:57:41.480
particle would have?

00:57:41.480 --> 00:57:43.350
If we had the state
a-plus, b-plus, c-plus,

00:57:43.350 --> 00:57:47.260
we would have 3 h bar over 2?

00:57:47.260 --> 00:57:48.240
PROFESSOR: No.

00:57:48.240 --> 00:57:52.770
The statement that
is done here is not

00:57:52.770 --> 00:57:59.140
that-- well, this is a
label for a particle.

00:57:59.140 --> 00:58:03.110
EPR just assumed
that if you measured

00:58:03.110 --> 00:58:05.700
a you would be able to get this.

00:58:05.700 --> 00:58:09.080
If you measure along
b, you would get this.

00:58:09.080 --> 00:58:12.090
And if you measured along
